-- Hundt Says Germany Jobless to Be Below 3 Million, Passauer Says
-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 2012-08-07T00:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-07/hundt-says-germany-jobless-to-be-below-3-million-passauer-says.html
Dieter Hundt, head of  Germany ’s BDA
employers’ association, said the number of unemployed in the
country will remain “considerably” below the three-million
mark this year,  Passauer Neue Presse  reported, citing an
interview.  The economic situation in Germany continues to be
“stable,” Hundt told the newspaper.  -- Editor: James Kraus  To contact the reporter on this story:
